This paper deals with the design and operation of DRAM chips, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of runtime profiling and error-correcting codes, which are relevant to embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents mechanisms for improving system performance, which could be relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
